# AI CONTEXT INSTRUCTOR
**CRITICAL:** Before answering architecture, workflow, database, or data source questions, and BEFORE starting any implementation, YOU MUST READ the files strictly inside `docs/ai_context/`.
Specifically:
- `docs/ai_context/01_architecture.md` (for how components interact)
- `docs/ai_context/02_data_sources.md` (for where we parse data from)
- `docs/ai_context/03_database_schema.md` (for database entities)
- `docs/ai_context/04_workflows.md` (for SOPs on how to add/edit features)
- `docs/ai_context/AI_CHANGELOG.md` (to understand what previous AI agents just did)

When you finish a complex task, ALWAYS log it into `docs/ai_context/AI_CHANGELOG.md` so the next AI agent knows what you did.

# GENERAL RULES

Always speak Russian.
Create all documents (plans, tasks, reports, artifacts) in Russian.
Main language of the user: Russian.

When you make code changes: always commit and push to origin (git add, git commit, git push).

В любом проекте проверяй наличие deploy-скриптов (deploy.sh, scripts/*.sh, .github/workflows и т.д.) — при необходимости деплоя запускай их, а не предполагай что доступа нет.

В HealthVault: не удалять debug-логирование в production ([day_stats], [targets], [avg_activity]) — оно помогает отладке и почти не занимает места.
